      • drive

        public void drive(double leftspeed,
         double rightspeed)
        Set the output for both motors
        Parameters:
        leftspeed - double ranging from -1.0 to 1.0, adding anything higher or lower will not cause errors and will automatically be adjusted. Left Motor is inverted and the Talon can only be inverted directly in the output.
        rightspeed - double ranging from -1.0 to 1.0, adding anything higher or lower will not cause errors and will automatically be adjusted.

      • deadband

        public double deadband(int axis,
              double deadband)
        Sets a dead band on a joystick axis to prevent constant power drain.
        Parameters:
        axis - The joystick axis to be used. The joystick is named "stick" and is initialized in robotInit.
        deadband - The dead band value. If the joystick is within the dead band, the function returns 0.
        Returns:
        If the joystick is within the dead band, returns 0. Otherwise, the negative of the axis will be returned because the joystick returns negative in the positive direction.
